                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d36">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/4264¾: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Phillips</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-06-30T13:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 30, 1940—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>271. Your 658, June 29, 7 p.m. Please say to King Alfonso that your Government
                    greatly appreciates his friendly and helpful message but that, in view of the
                    situation and present policies of this Government, it would seem better for the
                    purpose which the King has in mind for him to approach directly the Governments
                    immediately concerned.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
